Course Name: Diploma in Acting for Film and Television
Minimum Level of Education Required: Grade 12 with 50% and above
Scholarship Detail: Niagra Provides Schorlarship of CAD$1000 for students with IELTS score 7 and above
Remarks: Record your two audition pieces described above and a brief introduction (what the source of the audition piece is, the role you are playing and why you are performing it) for each piece. Upload the completed pieces to YouTube and send the YouTube link to acting@niagaracollege.ca (do not use the privacy setting). Please copy your YouTube link to rmcculloch@niagaracollege.ca and lravensborg@niagaracollege.ca   Also Please note : For your audition, pick two pieces (monologues) that are one and a half to two minutes in length each. Pick something that shows off who you are and the kind of actor youd like to become. The pieces should be contrasting and contemporary. For example: one could be dramatic and the other comedic. ? Choose something that is age appropriate. Would we believe you if you played this part? ? We want to see your version of whatever you choose; make it your own. Whats important to you? What do you love? ? The more prepared you are, the more confident youll be and the better chance youll have to let us see who you are. ? Understand that we may give you feedback or an adjustment and ask to see it again. ? And most important, enjoy the process. Have some fun with it. We love working with people who are committed to what they want and are ready to work toward it. And that starts with the audition process.   TOEFL: Niagra College comes under SPP (Student Partnership Program) program. TOEFL & PTE ARE NOT ACCEPTED AT SPP COLLEGES   Possible Career Opportunities Film and television Online, YouTube and web series production Commercials for radio, television and the Internet Industrial and corporate productions Voice-overs, narrations, cartoon animation Producing and entrepreneurial project development

Course Name: University Transfer Programme - UTP II in Science - Bachelor of Science
Minimum Level of Education Required: Students require Senior High School 12 equivalent: overall average of 65% with Chemistry 60%, Physics 60%, Biology 65% and Math 75%
Remarks: Students without Grade 12 equivalent Math or Biology will be admitted to the Science Fundamentals Program and  will be required to take MATH 100 and/or BIO 100 during their first term at FIC. These courses both count as Electives with academic credit and so students starting in the Science Fundamentals Program can still complete the  pathway in one year (three terms), provided they have enough electives available in their program to be used for  these classes.  Students without Grade 12 equivalent Chemistry or Physics are not eligible for admission to the Science pathway.  There is no UTP Stage I option available for students interested in Science.
